-- China's Top Climate Negotiator Says He Hopes U.S. Will Take Lead in Talks
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-23T03:03:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/china-s-top-climate-negotiator-says-he-hopes-u-s-will-take-lead-in-talks.html
China’s top climate negotiator Xie
Zhenhua said he hopes the U.S. will lead negotiations in moving
forward global climate change talks.  “We hope that the U.S. will take a leadership role to take
negotiations further forward,” Xie, a vice chairman of the
National Developement and Reform Commission, said at a briefing
in Beijing today. China and the U.S. are cooperating on clean-
energy technology and on climate change talks, Xie said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
